Can’t believe it’s now only one month until One Tin Bakes is out in the world! I cannot wait for you all to see it and get baking from it. This book was possible because of the massive support you gave me and my last book and it became my lockdown project, it’s what kept me going through the last year so a huge thank you for that.
-
The book is all about making baking as accessible as possible without compromising on flavour and interest, as the first line of the book says ‘easy does not mean boring’
-
Preordering is an easy way of supporting the book and the link in my bio will show you all the places you can get a copy including signed copies which can be preordered at @waterstones 
-
#onetinbakes #theboywhobakes #booklaunch #easybaking #sheetcake #slabpie #cookiegram #bakestagram #bakersofinstagram https://www.theboywhobakes.co.uk/onetinbakes

node.text:
Spending the last year at home has made me all the more aware of the amount of food that goes to waste, so I’m trying to use leftovers in creative ways and prevent as much excess waste as possible. This recipe was born from a fridge raid, I saw what leftovers we had and turned them into these delicious plant based muffins. I used @alpro Greek Style Plain as the base, which is naturally lower in saturated fat and made without added sugars, and I mixed that together with lots of bits from the fridge. You can take the base recipe and adapt it to whatever you have on hand that needs using up. When talking about waste we should also think about recycling and I know I’m not perfect but I’m trying to resuse any plastics we do use as much as possible and then recycle everything we cant, currently the @alpro packaging is 88% plant based and by 2025 it will be 100% recyclable.
-
Makes 6 muffins 
2 vegan eggs (2 tsp psyllium husk (or 2 tbsp ground flax seed) mixed with 6 tbsp water)
200g plain flour
1 tsp salt
3 tsp baking powder
2 tsp fennel seeds
2 tsp smoked paprika
3 vegan sausages, diced
Small handful parsley, finely chopped
Zest of 1 lemon
3 spring onions, sliced 
200ml @alpro Greek style plain
75ml @alpro soya drink
3 tsp chilli oil
Mixed seeds, for topping
-
Whisk together ingredients for vegan egg and set aside until thickened. Mix together flour, salt, baking powder, fennel seeds, paprika, sausages, parsley, lemon zest, spring onionsWhisk together @alpro Greek Style Plain, @alpro soya drink, chilli oil and vegan egg. Pour wet into dry and stir to form a thick batter. Divide between 6 tulip muffin cases (8 regular), sprinkle with seeds and bake at 180c (160c fan) for about 25 mins #goodforyou#plantpower #fridgeraid #theboywhobakes #savourybaking #savourymuffins #veganmuffins #veganbaking #bakersofinstagram

AD as it is currently @cakeweekuk I wanted to do a bakealong for my favourite nostalgic bake, a mash up of two recipes, a classic birthday cake. It’s one bowl vanilla cake and a take on classic fudge frosting. Recipes taken from my book One Tin Bakes. If you fancy winning a copy of the book check out @cakeweekuk’s account as they’re giving one away!
-
INGREDIENTS

One Bowl Vanilla Cake
400g plain flour 
1 1/4 tsp baking powder
2 1/2 tsp bicarbonate of soda 
1 tsp fine sea salt 
400g caster sugar 
3 large eggs 
135ml neutral tasting oil (or light olive)
285ml buttermilk
1 tsp vanilla bean paste 
240ml recently boiled water 

Fudge Frosting
340g unsalted butter 
120g icing sugar 
2 tbsp golden syrup or honey 
60g cocoa powder 
80ml sour cream 
80ml hot water 
200g dark chocolate, melted and cooled

This weeks bakealong from #OneTinBakes is the raspberry cheesecake streusel bars. They are really easy to make and so incredibly good, rich and tangy cheesecake infused with lemon and vanilla, sandwiched between a crunchy streusel layer and filled with a luscious raspberry mixture. Recipe is from the book and I will posting these videos regularly to build up a library of One Tin Bakes videos to help you guys bake from the book 👍

#ad Hey guys time for another bakealong! I’ve teamed up with @tateandlylesugars to show you a delicious small batch recipe, a passion fruit and coconut cake, which is perfectly suited to right now. It also keeps really well so even if there is only a two of you in the house they’ll be no waste. Ingredients are listed below and the instructions are in the video. 
60ml coconut oil (or melted butter, veg or olive oil)
60ml yoghurt (or buttermilk, kefir, sour cream)
20ml passion fruit puree (or any citrus juice)
2 large eggs 
125g @tateandlylesugars pure cane caster sugar 
Zest of 2 lime (or any citrus)
60g self raising flour
50g ground almonds
50g desiccated coconut (or semolina)
1/2 tsp baking powder 
100g @tateandlylesugars icing sugar 
Pulp from 1-2 passion fruit (or citrus juice)

Did you know it’s currently Sourdough September? A month celebrating and advocating for real sourdough, bread made with nothing but flour, water and salt (a campaign spearheaded by the @realbreadcampaign? You probably already know that I love baking with sourdough but what you don’t get from me very often is sweet sourdough recipes, enriched doughs, brioche recipes etc. Well today, in collaboration with @dovesfarm #, and in celebration of Sourdough September, I am showing you one of my all-time favourite sourdough recipes; Swedish cardamom buns. Link in my bio for the recipe

Can’t believe it’s now only one month until One Tin Bakes is out in the world! I cannot wait for you all to see it and get baking from it. This book was possible because of the massive support you gave me and my last book and it became my lockdown project, it’s what kept me going through the last year so a huge thank you for that.
-
The book is all about making baking as accessible as possible without compromising on flavour and interest, as the first line of the book says ‘easy does not mean boring’
-
Preordering is an easy way of supporting the book and the link in my bio will show you all the places you can get a copy including signed copies which can be preordered at @waterstones 
-
#onetinbakes #theboywhobakes #booklaunch #easybaking #sheetcake #slabpie #cookiegram #bakestagram #bakersofinstagram https://www.theboywhobakes.co.uk/onetinbakes
